==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[Argo]] [[navis]]'', the mythical "ship Argo"
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Argo Navis}}
'''[[Argo]] [[navis#Latin|Navis]]'''

#{{constellation}}: A former [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to represent the [[mythical]] [[ship]] [[Argo]]. In 1763, it was divided into the three new constellations: [[Carina]] (keel), [[Puppis]] (stern), and [[Vela]] (sail).

